Commentary Text: Mustafizur to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Chetan Sakariya!! Good catch at sweeper. But they are checking for a clean catch. It is. Waste of time. But that's what the IPL is all about. Saving time. Full outside off, Nitish Rana carves in the air and Sakariya dives forward to pouch it cleanly. Nitish Rana wants the catch to be checked and stands his ground, Pant isn't too pleased. Has a bit of a word or two to the departing batter after the catch is deemed clean. Nitish Rana c Chetan Sakariya b Mustafizur 57(34) [4s-3 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Kuldeep Yadav to Russell, out Stumped!! Poor from Russell and Pant gets lucky. He tries to make a statement against Kuldeep Yadav by charging out, the chinaman had shifted round the wicket to this ball, nicely tossed up and Russell is down the track to loft, misses as the ball keeps a bit low, Pant in his eagerness, fumbles the take but the ball falls off the glove onto the stumps with Russell well short. KKR in deep strife now. Not sure what Russell was thinking when he was not picking Kuldeep Yadav at all. Russell st Pant b Kuldeep Yadav 0(3)

Commentary Text: Kuldeep Yadav to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Pant!! That is the best keeper catch this season in the IPL. The googly from Kuldeep Yadav, pitches short and turns away, stays low outside off, Shreyas Iyer reaches out and does well to get a bottom-edge on the cut, it's going near Pant's bootlaces to his right, he sticks his right mitt out and hangs on. Went down due to his momentum giving away and was on the floor when he was appealing. Iyer knew he had edged it, waited for the clean catch confirmation and it was. What a catch that is. Shreyas Iyer c Pant b Kuldeep Yadav 42(37) [4s-4]

Commentary Text: Kuldeep Yadav to Narine, out Lbw!! DRS: Kolkata review an LBW. Oh this looks dead. Absolutely dead. And it is, three reds on ball-tracking. Kuldeep's back wrecking havoc against his former employers. It's the googly, which Narine completely misreads, looking to play it off the back foot after shuffling in front of his stumps. Commentary Text: Russell to Powell, out Axar Run Out!! 1 run completed. Needless! A wicket gifted to KKR. Just when Delhi seem to be pulling away they allow KKR back in the game. There was never a second in this and Axar is caught short by a long distance. Full toss on the pads and Powell gently nudges it into the mid-wicket, Shreyas swoops down and sends in a flat throw to the bowler's end. Venky Iyer collects the ball and breaks the stumps. Axar put in the dive/slide but it was not good enough. Axar run out (Shreyas Iyer/Venkatesh Iyer) 24(17) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Umesh Yadav to Warner, out Caught by Narine!! Good bouncer gets Warner. Right at the left-hander, who turns his head away as he pulls, but does not get timing or elevation to clear fine-leg where Narine moves to his right to take it. Umesh Yadav was brought back to get the wicket and he does just that. Fifth time Umesh has dismissed Warner - the most a bowler has got Warner out in IPL. Can KKR build on this wicket further? Warner c Narine b Umesh Yadav 42(26) [4s-8]
